      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is exhausting to keep performing normalcy when inside you're crumbling, and you're right, writing won't magically fill the space he left. That gray feeling you're describing is the natural state of deep grief, and fighting it is just adding more strain to an already broken system. If pretending is too much, maybe you could just give yourself permission to stop pretending, even if that means letting the exhaustion win for a while.",
      "source": "target",
